      • exec

        public BugReport exec(TerminalScanner scan,
                      DataModel model,
                      User user)
               throws PermissionException,
                      CancelException,
                      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Execute this command and possibly return a result.


        1. The developer indicates he wants to assign a developer to a bug report.
        2. Include use case Select Bug Report if required.
        3. The system shows a list of developers that are involved in the project.
        4. The logged in developer selects one or more of the developers to assign to the selected bug report on top of those already assigned.
        5. The systems assigns the selected developers to the selected bug report.
        Extensions:
        3a. The selected bug report is of a project that the logged in developer is not involved in as lead or tester.
        1. The use case returns to step 2.

        Specified by:
        exec in interface Cmd<BugReport>
        Parameters:
        scan - The TerminalScanner used to interact with the person.
        model - The DataModel used for model access.
        user - The User who wants to executes this command.
        Returns:
        The BugReport selected to assign users to.
        Throws:
        PermissionException - When the user does not have sufficient permissions.
        CancelException - When the users wants to abort the current cmd
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - When scan, model,user is null
        See Also:
        DataModel.addUsersToBugReport(User, BugReport, PList)
